###########################################################################
#  eq_aligned_proof - a four-line algebraic derivation typeset as a       #
#  left-aligned vertical pile via `labove`.  Companion to eq_alignment,  #
#  which uses a `matrix row rcol/ccol/lcol` to align two equations on   #
#  the equals sign; this snippet uses the simpler `labove` chain to     #
#  stack a chain of justified-by-reason derivation steps.               #
###########################################################################

@SysInclude { eq }
@SysInclude { doc }
@Doc @Text @Begin
@PP
A short algebraic derivation, each line left-aligned under the previous:
@DP
@CentredDisplay @Eq {
   { ( x + 1 ) sup 2 }
   labove { = ( x + 1 ) ( x + 1 ) }
   labove { = x sup 2 + x + x + 1 }
   labove { = x sup 2 + 2 x + 1 }
}
@End @Text
